Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: https://i.imgur.com/7bgbDpN.png

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: 3x 22MB files sent over streamer, all were able to be extracted from blockchain using an RPC call. 😄

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: This thing is totally limited by network bandwidth, at least on a RYZEN 2700X CPU, and I am using only 1/4 of that CPU to do this.

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: Leaves plenty left over to encode the video stream.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: @blackjok3r Awesome update mate!!

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: Video streaming via blockchain!!! 😃

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: Yeah its been a long couple of days to get that RPC working... had to rethink strategy half way through and go back and change the way I was sending data.

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: But its really really fast and efficiant.

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: Can handle more than 1 stream per chain. But if there was too many finding them would prove a little hard ... seek though blocks and look for small ones, theres always a small block, where it charges up the blaster before the next stream begins.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: streaming as in youtube. data on top of a blockchain. data in the blocks. in chunks.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: the kinda streaming which no authority can block

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: and each part or bit of that video leaves a proof on the blockchain how it was at the time of streaming.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: example, can redirect live tv video to a video streaming chain. anything going in that stream is always be there till at least that copy of blockchain exists.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: a single blockchain won't be enough for this
